column5: Southern Ontario is going to get a noreaster tonite. Nothing major by the looks of the thing, but it is there none the less. Should make Lake O a mess later.
And what will it do to the fishing - o great forecasting one?

I don't know about where you folks are but for about 80KM around me the winds from this so called nor easter are a going to be a WHOOPING 15KM per hour from the southWEST that should really stir things up..... or probably not? By morning the winds where I want to go fishing are supposed to be southwest 10KM..  So where is this nor easter coming from?

Bring it on home...we need the rain here in kitchener!!! The radar shows lots of it, but the forecasts from both Enviroment Canada, and the weather network show only a little bit is expected... I hope they are WAY wrong
Do you really think the weather people could possibly  be wrong cookslav?
